Hi everyone,

We have created a modules with different fields that act as a settings for our module and then we put a  value on the “template” like

```slider_settings={
  "items_to_show_per_slide": 3
}```
but when we create a page using that template.. the fields are disabled and when we inspect the editor of the page it is showing this error

```Uncaught TypeError: Cannot create property 'items_to_show_per_slide' on string '{
   "items_to_show_per_slide": 3 
}'```
so we have tried to make it like this instead without the double quote:

```slider_settings={
   items_to_show_per_slide: 3
}```
and this solves the issue, however we are kind of confused cause on other scenario like this

```style_options={
      background_color: { 
             "color": "#243241", 
             "opacity": 100 
       }
}```
when we create a page with that options declared on the template.. the module is working fine and we are able to edit the options inside the module.

is there a rule in putting a quote on the module field when we are adding a value in the template?
